    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-09-17T05:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-09-17T05:35:00-05:00" n="50"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d50">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4 A 2/91: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-09-17T14:00:00+03:25">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 17, 1924—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:31 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>120. Department’s 65, August 13, 4 p.m.<note n="86" xml:id="d50fn86">Not printed;
                        see despatch no. 652, Sept. 23, from the Chargé in Persia, <ref
                            target="frus1924v02#pg_588">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p.
                            588</ref>.</note> and 83, September 15, 5 p.m. I learned informally this
                    morning from Dr. Millspaugh that the Persian Government has decided to send
                    Mirza Eissa Khan to represent Persia at the forthcoming opium conference at
                    Geneva in <pb facs="0215" n="101" xml:id="pg_101"/> November. This Persian is at
                    present the Persian Government Commissioner with the Anglo-Persian Oil Company
                    in London.</p>
                <p>Legation will transmit by next pouch to the Department full report on the opium
                    situation in Persia based on data Dr. Millspaugh has kindly offered to supply
                        me.<note n="87" xml:id="d50fn87">The report, prepared by Col. D. W.
                        MacCormack of the American Financial Mission in Persia and submitted to the
                        Second Opium Conference by the Persian delegation, is printed in League of
                        Nations, <hi rend="italic">Records of the Second Opium Conference, Geneva,
                            November 17th, 1924–February 19th, 1925</hi>, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >ii</hi>, p. 194.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
